sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as Gateway / Ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Predictor as Model Server<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1: InferenceService Model Serving (Raw Kubernetes)

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/models/{name}:predict<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    GW->>KRBP: Forward to Service<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS
    KRBP->>KRBP: SubjectAccessReview<br/>on InferenceService resource
    KRBP->>Predictor: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8080 (pod-local)
    Predictor->>Storage: Load model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, Provider creds
    Storage-->>Predictor: Model artifacts
    Predictor-->>KRBP: Prediction response (JSON)
    KRBP-->>GW: Response
    GW-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 2: LLMInferenceService with Gateway API

    participant GW2 as Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant EPP as Scheduler EPP<br/>gRPC/TCP TLS
    participant LLMPod as vLLM Workload<br/>8000/TCP HTTPS

    Client->>GW2: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    GW2->>EPP: Route via InferencePool<br/>gRPC, TLS (self-signed), Bearer token
    EPP->>EPP: Scheduling decision<br/>(prefill/decode routing)
    EPP->>LLMPod: Forward to workload<br/>HTTPS/8000, TLS (self-signed)
    LLMPod->>Storage: Load model<br/>HTTPS/443, Provider creds
    Storage-->>LLMPod: Model artifacts
    LLMPod-->>EPP: Streaming response
    EPP-->>GW2: gRPC response
    GW2-->>Client: SSE / JSON response

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 3: InferenceGraph Routing

    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Router as kserve-router<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant ISVC1 as InferenceService A<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant ISVC2 as InferenceService B<br/>80/TCP HTTP

    Client->>Route: POST inference request<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS Reencrypt
    Route->>Router: Forward<br/>HTTPS/443 or HTTP/8080, Optional bearer
    Router->>ISVC1: Splitter/Ensemble node<br/>HTTP/80 (in-mesh mTLS)
    Router->>ISVC2: Parallel (Ensemble) or<br/>Sequential (Sequence)<br/>HTTP/80 (in-mesh mTLS)
    ISVC1-->>Router: Prediction A
    ISVC2-->>Router: Prediction B
    Router->>Router: Combine results<br/>(Ensemble/Sequence logic)
    Router-->>Route: Combined response
    Route-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 4: LocalModel Cache Distribution

    participant LMCtrl as LocalModel Controller<br/>HTTPS/443
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP
    participant LMAgent as LocalModelNode Agent<br/>DaemonSet
    participant NodeFS as Node Filesystem<br/>(PV)

    LMCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create PV/PVC<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    LMAgent->>K8sAPI: Create download Job<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>LMAgent: Job created
    LMAgent->>Storage: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, Credentials from Secret
    Storage-->>LMAgent: Model files
    LMAgent->>NodeFS: Write to local PV<br/>Filesystem, POSIX permissions
